race.comment: LOVE TO ALL (6) was close up when finishing second here fresh from a spell, and then ran on too late for third at Warwick a fortnight ago. Her only career win has been when third up from a spell, and she looks perfectly placed to get the job done this time. QICKWIT (3) is heading the right way with her form and was less than a length from the winner when runner-up here nearly 3 weeks ago. He slides down in class this time and can go one better. WORLDY SPIRIT (12) followed up a big effort fresh up here at long odds, with a game win by a head at Dalby in her penultimate start. She ran on late last time out at Toowoomba, and is likely to be hitting the line hard here as well. If the pace is genuine, then she can have the last say. SURCOTE (7) left his run too late over 1015m at Ballina a fortnight ago, and he has not missed a cheque in 3 starts over this trip. Stick with him at some each-way value. EXTREME ALLY (8) was second at her Queensland debut, and can take this out. Each way.
